          "text": "The central interception points are:  \n1.\n\n`tcp_recv_slot` uses SSL_read when the slot has TLS.  \n`send_all_nb` uses SSL_write when the file descriptor is TLS, requiring a mapping from fd to slot or passing the slot directly.  \n\nOn accept in `proxy_accept_batch`, the C function `httpd_tls_accept_slot(slot)` from Li is called. Since `proxy_accept_batch` is in Li, an extern procedure for TLS accept must be added after `tcp_accept_nb`.  \n\nThe following additions are needed:  \n- `httpd_tls_runtime_enabled_i()` returns 1 if TLS termination is configured  \n- `httpd_tls_accept_conn_i(conn_fd, slot)` performs the handshake, returning 0 on success, -1 on failure, and sets ALPN in the slot  \n- `tcp_recv_slot` and `send_all_nb` are modified to check `g_slot_tls[slot]`\n\nFor `send_all_nb`, since it uses connection fd instead of slot, the slot must be found by fd or stored in a map keyed by fd. A better approach uses parallel arrays for SSL context and protocol type indexed by slot. `send_all_nb` can then use `httpd_slot_find_fd(conn)` to retrieve the slot and perform SSL write. For H2 mode, `tcp_recv_slot` cannot be used identically because `proxy_handle_client_in` expects HTTP/1 headers in the slot buffer.\n\nFor H2, early handling in the `httpd_tls_accept_conn_i` flow or a dedicated `httpd_h2_poll_slot_i(slot)` called from Li instead of `proxy_handle_client_in` is required.\n\nAdd to lib.li `proxy_accept_batch`:\n```\nif httpd_tls_slot_h2_i(slot) == 1:\n  httpd_h2_serve_slot_i(epfd, slot)\n  return accepted\n```\n\nImplement files using dlopen for OpenSSL to avoid requiring libssl-dev. Create `li_rt_tls.c` with comprehensive OpenSSL function types via dlopen.\n\nFor build linking:\n- Add `li_rt_tls.c` to compile when `needs_rt_net`\n- Link `-ldl` always on Linux\n\nTLS mode now uses runtime linking with dlopen for libssl.so.3, avoiding compile-time dependencies. It loads symbols dynamically and initializes OpenSSL, with an LI_HTTPD_TLS=1 check to handle dlopen failures during startup. The implementation is in li_rt_tls.c, which includes dlopen logic and function pointer setup for OpenSSL functions.\n\nThe TLS context is created using TLS_server_method with a minimum of TLS 1.3, and the certificate and key are loaded. ALPN protocols are set to prioritize HTTP/2 and HTTP/1.1. The `li_rt_tls_handshake_slot` function establishes a TLS handshake, determines the negotiated protocol via ALPN, and stores the corresponding protocol version and SSL context in global arrays indexed by slot.\n\nFor `li_rt_h2.c`, each slot maintains its own state, stored in `g_h2_state[slot]`.",
