        "type": "thinkingMessage",
        "message": {
          "text": "The HPACK indexed header fix requires adding 1 to the index since the RFC static table uses 1-based indexing, while h2_read_int returns the index from wire format with an existing offset.\n\nFor indexed header fields, the index value equals 1 plus the value from integer encoding. For example, index 2 (GET) has wire value 0x82 = 128 + 2, where 0x82 = 10000010 with prefix 7 and value 2. The static table index 2 corresponds to GET. The fix for h2_send_response HPACK uses 0x88 for index 8, which represents \":status 200\" with value \"200\". A TOML example and test script should be created. Additionally, fix h2 after failed handshake by calling epoll_del before close in httpd_client_force_close_i.\n\nWhen a TLS handshake fails in proxy_accept_batch, tcp_close is called followed by httpd_slot_free, but the file descriptor might be closed twice. Since the connection was added to epoll, epoll_ctl_del_i should be called before closing the connection and freeing the slot. The fix involves calling epoll_ctl_del_i on the epoll file descriptor, then tcp_close, and finally httpd_slot_free. This ensures proper cleanup order and prevents double closing of the file descriptor.\n\nWhen h2 serves, httpd_client_force_close_i should epoll del, as httpd_conn_close_slot handles this when epfd >= 0. For the h2 path, passing epfd is correct.\n\nCreate a tls_h2.toml example and test script.\n\nUpdate plan yaml m2-tls-h2-runtime to completed.\n\nRelease notes.\n\nhttpd-plan-gates.sh hook.\n\nRun build and tests.\n\nFix SSL error codes: OPENSSL 3 uses SSL_ERROR_WANT_READ = 2 and WANT_WRITE = 3.\n\nFix li_rt_h2: ensure END_STREAM flag 0x01 is correctly applied to DATA frames, and END_HEADERS = 0x04 for HEADERS frames.",
